    "body": "These still come from the locally built images.  The docker image build process did get changed though in https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/8242 so that there's a single `Dockerfile`. The build process for all the binaries reuses a heap of work so there's now a single build process that builds everything then it just copies the required executable into separate docker images for each component.  So the `Dockerfile` I think you're looking for is `ops/docker/op-stack-go/Dockerfile`.\r\n\r\nThe `docker-bake.hcl` in the top level is also a useful reference since that's the entry point to it all.  And you can use `make golang-docker` to build the images locally.",
